# Progress Report (Condensed)

**Purpose:** Document and communicate research progress.

**Links to:** milestone-tracker, experiment-tracking, thesis-writing, paper-writing

---

## Report Types

### 1. Monthly Advisor Report (1-2 pages)
- Summary, accomplishments, key results, blockers, plan, questions

### 2. Committee Meeting Report (3-5 pages)
- Executive summary, completed/current work, timeline, publications, risks, questions

### 3. Annual Report (5-10 pages)
- Overview, literature, methodology, results, publications, teaching, timeline

### 4. Funding Agency Report
- Executive summary, technical progress, publications, budget, plan

## Monthly Report Template

```markdown
# Monthly Progress Report — [Month Year]

## Summary
[2-3 sentences]

## Accomplishments
- [ ] [Task] — [Status]

## Key Results
| Experiment | Metric | Result |
|------------|--------|--------|

## Blockers
- [Blocker] → [Solution]

## Next Month Plan
| Week | Task | Deliverable |
|------|------|-------------|

## Questions for Advisor
1. [Question]
```

## Committee Report Template

```markdown
# Committee Meeting Report — [Date]

## Executive Summary
[1 paragraph]

## Timeline Status
| Milestone | Target | Actual | Status |
|-----------|--------|--------|--------|

## Publications
| Paper | Venue | Status |

## Challenges & Risks
| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |

## Questions for Committee
```

## Meeting Preparation

Before advisor:
- [ ] Review last goals, prepare results, list blockers, draft plan

Before committee:
- [ ] All above + slides (10-15 min), update literature, prepare demo

## Email Template

Subject: PhD Progress Report — [Month]
Body: highlights, questions, attach report
